13 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 240.2 of Title 44, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Construction or modification of a facility structure may not
17 encroach upon or otherwise have an adverse impact on the mission,
18 training, or operations of any military installation or branch of
19 the military as determined by the Clearinghouse and the FAA.
20 B. An adverse impact to a military installation or branch of
21 the military as described in subsection A of this section includes
22 an adverse impact to:
23 1. A military training route;
24 2. A drop zone;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2142 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 3. An approach to a runway;
2 4. A test or training range;
3 5. A military installation or facility;
4 6. United States Department of Defense special use air space;
5 and
6 7. United States Department of Defense spectral requirements.
7 C. A facility structure may not be constructed or expanded
8 unless:
9 1. There is an active determination of no hazard; or
10 2. Any adverse impacts to the United States Department of
11 Defense, determined in accordance with 32 C.F.R., Section 211.6, or
12 the National Defense Authorization Act have been resolved as
13 evidenced by documentation from the Clearinghouse for the facility
14 structure and the Department.
15 D. For purposes of paragraph 2 of subsection C of this section,
16 a mission compatibility certification letter may serve as evidence
17 that the wind energy facility has resolved adverse impacts with the
18 United States Department of Defense or successor agency.
19 E. Before expanding or constructing a facility structure, and
20 within thirty (30) days of submitting an application to the FAA, an
21 owner shall file a copy of the FAA application with the Department.
22 F. Within fifteen (15) days of receiving a copy of the FAA
23 application to construct a wind energy site, the Oklahoma Military
24
