1 Depa rtment will provide a copy of the application to the affected
2 military entities.
3 G. The Department may serve in a coordination role with the
4 owner and the affected military entity.
5 H. Within thirty (30) days of receiving final notification from
6 the FAA or a Notice of Presumed Risk from the Department of Defense,
7 the owner shall provide the Department a copy of the documentation.
8 I. The Department may make rules in accordance with the
9 Oklahoma Administrative Procedures Act to administer this section.
10 J. The documentation an owner submits in accordance with
11 subsections E and H of this section:
12 1. Shall only be used and disclosed by the Department in
13 accordance with this section;
14 2. Is confidential, not public, and not open to public
15 inspection; and
16 3. Is not subject to the Oklahoma Open Records Act.
17 K. If an owner fails to submit the documentation described in
18 subsections E and H of this section for an individual facility
19 structure:
20 1. The Department may charge the owner an administrative
21 penalty not to exceed One Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($1,500.00)
22 per day, per violation; and
23 2. A stakeholder, including the Department, may bring an action
24 in court to:
